Class GroupCmd

java.lang.Object
LibraryCommand
GroupCmd
public class GroupCmd
extends LibraryCommand
Class for Command Group, this command is to print all the books of a Library grouped by author or title, depending on the modality chosen by the author (with the command).

  • Constructor Details

    • GroupCmd

      public GroupCmd​(java.lang.String ArgumentInput)
      Constructor of the class, it creates a Group Command. It calls the super Class constructor using as parameters the CommandType GROUP and the ArgumentInput. This SuperClass Constructor will call the overridden method parseArguments to try to initialize the fields of the created Group Command.
      Parameters:
      ArgumentInput - String given by the user. It is expected to take the value of either AUTHOR or TITLE.

  • Method Details

    • execute

      public void execute​(LibraryData data)
      Overridden method that is used to execute the command Group. if the given Library is not empty it will try to order the books in groups using a helper method. If it is empty it will print a message to the user.
      Specified by:
      execute in class LibraryCommand
      Parameters:
      data - book data to be considered for command execution.
      Throws:
      java.lang.NullPointerException - if the given LibraryData is null or if the command is null.

    • groupData

      private void groupData​(java.util.List<BookEntry> books)
      Private Method that is used as a helper Method in execute. This method is used to iterate over the books and to create a hashMap that will held the information about the groups, each key of the hashMap will be linked to a different group This method uses two helper methods in function of what type of group has been chosen by the user.
      Parameters:
      books - is the list of books contained in the given Library, to enter this method it must not be empty.

    • executeGroupByTitle

      private void executeGroupByTitle​(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.util.List<java.lang.String>> groupedData, BookEntry book)
      Private method used as a helper method of groupData, this method is only evoked when the command is equal to TITLE, in this case the method will try to organise all the books in groups by title in a hashMap for that the key will be the first letter of the title or the numeric group if the first character is a number. (The group should be case-insensitive).
      Parameters:
      groupedData - HashMap that contains all the different groups of books.
      book - BookEntry that is going to be analysed and added to the hashMap.

    • executeGroupByAuthor

      private void executeGroupByAuthor​(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.util.List<java.lang.String>> groupedData, BookEntry book)
      This method is used as a Helper method of GroupData, it is only evoked when the command is equal to AUTHOR. In this case the method will create a key for each author that has written the book, so a book can appear in more than one group
      Parameters:
      groupedData - HashMap that contains all the different groups of book`s titles.
      book - BookEntry that is going to be analysed and added to the hashMap.

    • addBookToHashMapAndToKeys

      private void addBookToHashMapAndToKeys​(java.lang.String key, java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.util.List<java.lang.String>> GroupedData, BookEntry book)
      Private Method that is used in both executeGroupByAuthor and executeGroupByTitle, This method given a key and a hashMap it will look if the key is already in the hashMap and if it is not it will add the key and the value, if the key is already there it will add the value to the list of values(titles) that is linked to such key. If the key is not in the hashMap it will update the list keys.
      Parameters:
      key - group were the title of the book is going to be added.
      GroupedData - HashMap that contains all the different groups of book`s titles.
      book - BookEntry that is going to be analysed and added to the hashMap.

    • executePrinting

      private void executePrinting​(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.util.List<java.lang.String>> groupedData, java.util.List<java.lang.String> keys)
      Private Method that is used in execute. This method is used to print all the contents in of a HashMap, taking into account the order given by the List of keys (that has been previously ordered)
      Parameters:
      groupedData - HashMap that contains all the different groups of book`s titles.
      keys - List of all the keys (this will be used to print in the correct order all the groups).

    • parseArguments

      protected boolean parseArguments​(java.lang.String argumentInput)
      Overridden Method used to determine if the user's input is valid. For that the first condition is that the argument is not null, it should also take into account if it is one of the accepted commands(AUTHOR or TITLE).
      Overrides:
      parseArguments in class LibraryCommand
      Parameters:
      argumentInput - argument input for this command
      Returns:
      true if the Argument has passed all the tests and false otherwise.
      Throws:
      java.lang.NullPointerException - if the given Argument is null.

    • parseCommandOption

      private boolean parseCommandOption​(java.lang.String option)
      Private Method uses as a Helper method in parseArguments. This method is used to determine if the given argument matches one of the two accepted command values that are of the type CommandOptions, and can have the values of AUTHOR or TITLE
      Parameters:
      option - argument input given by the user.
      Returns:
      true if the input matches one of the two command options and false otherwise.
